If you give a box of See's
chocolates to your girlfriend

00:39:52.079 --> 00:39:54.773
on the first date
and she kisses you?

00:39:54.973 --> 00:39:56.990
We own you.
You know? I mean we...

00:39:57.190 --> 00:39:58.724
we can raise
the price tomorrow.

00:39:58.924 --> 00:40:00.258
I mean,
you'll buy the same box.

00:40:00.458 --> 00:40:02.083
You're not gonna
fool around with success,

00:40:02.283 --> 00:40:04.800
so the key there
is the response.

00:40:05.000 --> 00:40:08.208
You do not want to get home
on Valentine's Day

00:40:08.408 --> 00:40:10.291
and say to your wife
or your sweetheart...

00:40:10.491 --> 00:40:12.634
preferably they're
the same person...

00:40:12.834 --> 00:40:15.667
you don't say, "Here, honey,
I took the low bid."

00:40:15.867 --> 00:40:16.966
It doesn't work.

00:40:17.166 --> 00:40:20.083
Price is...
to a degree, is immaterial.

00:40:20.283 --> 00:40:22.258
If you've got
an economic castle,

00:40:22.458 --> 00:40:25.250
people are gonna come and wanna
take that castle away from you.

00:40:25.450 --> 00:40:26.800
You better have
a strong moat.

00:40:27.000 --> 00:40:29.750
You better have a knight in the
castle that knows what he's doing.

00:40:31.166 --> 00:40:32.508
You're not buying an asset,

00:40:32.708 --> 00:40:35.000
you're buying a name,
you're buying a brand,

00:40:35.200 --> 00:40:37.675
you're buying
a real franchise here,

00:40:37.875 --> 00:40:42.834
and Charlie was more responsible
for that than anybody.

