01:09:56.166 --> 01:09:58.583
It worked well,
but I don't think it'll work

01:09:58.783 --> 01:10:00.750
for lots of other people
necessarily.

01:10:02.583 --> 01:10:04.592
Susie and I loved each other,
we admired each other,

01:10:04.792 --> 01:10:07.458
and we were totally in sync
with what the other was doing,

01:10:07.658 --> 01:10:09.875
but we were
two different individuals.

01:10:12.458 --> 01:10:14.966
????

01:10:15.166 --> 01:10:19.083
Susie: The first time Warren
came out to San Francisco...

01:10:20.083 --> 01:10:22.150
we took a walk,
and he looked around,

01:10:22.350 --> 01:10:24.417
and he doesn't...
he's not very visual.

01:10:25.375 --> 01:10:27.941
He was looking around,
and he said,

01:10:28.141 --> 01:10:30.708
"This really is...
this is your city."

01:10:37.625 --> 01:10:42.583
I am so drawn to color,
light, form, and nature,

01:10:42.783 --> 01:10:46.500
that he thought
it was a good place for me.

01:10:47.875 --> 01:10:49.671
Warren:
Over the years I've developed

01:10:49.871 --> 01:10:51.467
a better understanding
of human nature.

01:10:51.667 --> 01:10:53.383
I can learn a lot about
investments out of a book,

01:10:53.583 --> 01:10:57.375
but I don't think you can learn
as much about human beings.

01:10:57.575 --> 01:10:58.759
You really need
some experiences,

01:10:58.959 --> 01:11:03.250
and I'm wiser in that respect
than I was 40 or 50 years ago,

01:11:03.450 --> 01:11:05.791
even though
I can't rattle off numbers

01:11:05.991 --> 01:11:08.333
the same way
I used to be able to.

01:11:08.533 --> 01:11:10.750
????

01:11:13.875 --> 01:11:18.500
Well, I think that what we do
reflects who we are,

01:11:18.700 --> 01:11:20.750
and that's true for everybody
in this room.

01:11:20.950 --> 01:11:23.175
And if you do the work I do,

01:11:23.375 --> 01:11:25.875
you meet the best
human beings in the world.

01:11:26.075 --> 01:11:27.800
People who
have made a choice

01:11:28.000 --> 01:11:31.296
not to make money,
but to serve other human beings.

01:11:31.496 --> 01:11:34.592
I think it's the best kind
of life anyone could have.

01:11:34.792 --> 01:11:39.583
I was with her in Arizona at this "Fortune"
Most Powerful Women's Conference,

01:11:39.783 --> 01:11:42.041
and she told me she had
a biopsy the day before,

01:11:42.241 --> 01:11:44.083
and I didn't really think
much of it.

01:11:44.283 --> 01:11:46.008
????

01:11:46.208 --> 01:11:49.375
Then we got home,
and the biopsy results were not good.

01:11:49.575 --> 01:11:51.208
It was stage four
oral cancer.

01:11:53.041 --> 01:11:55.959
Howard:
I was on my way to a board meeting in India,

01:11:56.159 --> 01:11:57.750
and I remember
saying to her,

01:11:57.950 --> 01:11:59.542
"I'll see you
when I get back."

01:11:59.742 --> 01:12:01.300
And she rarely cried,

01:12:01.500 --> 01:12:03.250
and she just
started crying and said,

01:12:03.450 --> 01:12:04.592
"No, you need to stay here,

01:12:04.792 --> 01:12:07.208
and you need to come out
for the operation."

01:12:09.083 --> 01:12:10.759
Susie Jr.:
So we were all there,

01:12:10.959 --> 01:12:13.583
and the day she was
going into the surgery,

01:12:13.783 --> 01:12:16.925
that morning,
my dad...

01:12:17.125 --> 01:12:20.000
It's funny, he...
there's some of it he just can't...

01:12:20.200 --> 01:12:21.217
you know, he just can't...

01:12:21.417 --> 01:12:24.625
the thought of something happening
to her was just, for him...

01:12:24.825 --> 01:12:27.625
you know,
was just the worst thing that could happen.

01:12:27.825 --> 01:12:28.717
????

01:12:28.917 --> 01:12:31.083
Peter:
She knew it was going to be really difficult.

01:12:31.283 --> 01:12:34.895
She knew the recovery
was going to be brutal,

01:12:35.095 --> 01:12:38.708
so I think that she had
that surgery for others.

01:12:42.000 --> 01:12:44.425
It was...
quite a big surgery.

01:12:44.625 --> 01:12:48.625
She couldn't talk,
she couldn't swallow, she couldn't eat.

01:12:48.825 --> 01:12:51.917
But she came out,
and I really was with her

01:12:52.117 --> 01:12:53.708
for the next
four months or so.

01:12:54.834 --> 01:12:56.417
And my dad came out
every weekend.

01:12:56.617 --> 01:12:58.625
????

01:13:02.834 --> 01:13:05.458
And in a few months
she was doing better.

01:13:16.834 --> 01:13:18.508
She and my dad had gone
to Cody, Wyoming,

01:13:18.708 --> 01:13:21.458
which they did every year
with a bunch of friends.

01:13:26.500 --> 01:13:31.500
And my dad called. This was,
I don't know, 8:00 at night or something,

01:13:31.700 --> 01:13:34.646
and he said,
"Something happened to Mom.

01:13:34.846 --> 01:13:37.792
I'm in an ambulance.
You need to come."

01:13:41.500 --> 01:13:44.191
Howard: I actually thought
something had happened to my dad.

01:13:44.391 --> 01:13:47.083
I don't know why I thought that,
but I... I guess I thought

01:13:47.283 --> 01:13:48.759
my mom had
had this recovery,

01:13:48.959 --> 01:13:53.291
it was successful,
and why would anything happen to her?

01:13:53.491 --> 01:13:56.792
????

01:13:59.083 --> 01:14:00.166
It was horrible.

01:14:01.458 --> 01:14:02.800
And a total shock.

01:14:03.000 --> 01:14:04.675
You know, she'd been fine.

01:14:04.875 --> 01:14:06.733
She'd been fine.
They went off to Cody,

01:14:06.933 --> 01:14:08.592
she was fine,
and they were having dinner,

01:14:08.792 --> 01:14:11.625
and you know,
she didn't feel well after dinner,

01:14:11.825 --> 01:14:14.333
and... she had the stroke.

01:14:19.208 --> 01:14:22.625
We went into the hospital room,
and my dad was sitting there.

01:14:22.825 --> 01:14:25.625
He'd been sitting there
all night, holding her hand.

01:14:28.000 --> 01:14:29.550
I was so proud of him,

01:14:29.750 --> 01:14:31.712
because when
it came down to it,

01:14:31.912 --> 01:14:33.675
he knew what
he was supposed to do,

01:14:33.875 --> 01:14:36.542
and he did it,
which was nothing.

01:14:36.742 --> 01:14:39.708
????

01:14:40.750 --> 01:14:43.041
So my dad went to sleep,

01:14:43.241 --> 01:14:44.550
and I sat with her.

01:14:44.750 --> 01:14:47.375
And I just kept
putting my hand on her heart

01:14:47.575 --> 01:14:49.792
to see if she was
breathing, and...

01:14:52.125 --> 01:14:54.708
At one point, you know,
I didn't feel anything,

01:14:54.908 --> 01:14:56.645
so I went out,
I got the nurse,

01:14:56.845 --> 01:14:58.781
and I said,
"Can you come in here?"

01:14:58.981 --> 01:15:00.717
And she said,
"No, she's gone."

01:15:00.917 --> 01:15:03.417
So, I have to say one
of the worst moments of my life

01:15:03.617 --> 01:15:05.083
was waking my dad up
to tell him that.

01:15:05.283 --> 01:15:08.250
????

01:15:15.458 --> 01:15:16.917
Warren:
It's a very strange thing, love.

01:15:17.117 --> 01:15:18.041
You can't get rid of it.

01:15:20.500 --> 01:15:22.667
If you try to give it out,
you get more back.

01:15:25.166 --> 01:15:27.083
If you try to hang onto it,
you lose it.

01:15:36.000 --> 01:15:39.208
Susie...
really put me together.

01:15:39.408 --> 01:15:40.133
She believed in me.

01:15:40.333 --> 01:15:42.091
She-she-she...
she put me together.

01:15:42.291 --> 01:15:46.291
And I would not only have turned out
to be the person I turned out to be,

01:15:46.491 --> 01:15:47.717
but I would not have...

01:15:47.917 --> 01:15:50.792
I actually wouldn't have been as successful
in business without that, and...

01:15:51.583 --> 01:15:53.250
she made me more
of a whole person.

01:15:53.450 --> 01:15:55.959
????

01:16:01.083 --> 01:16:05.125
Peter: He went dark,
essentially, quiet and inward

01:16:05.325 --> 01:16:06.750
for a certain amount
of time.

01:16:06.950 --> 01:16:09.175
????

01:16:09.375 --> 01:16:12.258
You know, my dad is
a solitary guy,

01:16:12.458 --> 01:16:16.792
and he had lived, essentially,
a solitary life in a lot of ways.

01:16:19.166 --> 01:16:22.233
I think it came down
to him figuring out

01:16:22.433 --> 01:16:25.500
how he was gonna
get through this tunnel

01:16:25.700 --> 01:16:27.583
and get out the other side.

01:16:32.000 --> 01:16:33.133
In my head
at the time, I thought,

01:16:33.333 --> 01:16:35.625
"God, I don't know
if he'll ever get out of bed."

01:16:39.333 --> 01:16:40.625
But he did.

01:16:53.375 --> 01:16:55.383
Welcome.
I'm Patty Stonesifer,

01:16:55.583 --> 01:16:58.166
the CEO of the Bill
and Melinda Gates Foundation.

01:16:58.366 --> 01:16:59.966
And we appreciate
you coming today,

01:17:00.166 --> 01:17:03.358
especially since I sent a very
vague and very late notice

01:17:03.558 --> 01:17:06.750
to ask you to come to a
conversation with Bill and Melinda

01:17:06.950 --> 01:17:09.291
on the future on philanthropy.

01:17:09.491 --> 01:17:11.717
So, lets get on with it.

01:17:11.917 --> 01:17:15.841
I have the pleasure
of introducing a good man

01:17:16.041 --> 01:17:20.667
whose great decision is going to
change the world, Warren Buffett.

01:17:26.500 --> 01:17:29.125
????

01:17:31.375 --> 01:17:33.050
Man:
A remarkable decision tonight

01:17:33.250 --> 01:17:35.208
from one of the richest men
in the world.

01:17:35.408 --> 01:17:37.175
Mega-billionaire
Warren Buffett says

01:17:37.375 --> 01:17:40.208
he is giving away most of
his fortune away to charity.

01:17:40.408 --> 01:17:41.875
Woman:
Buffett has pledged to give away

01:17:42.075 --> 01:17:43.258
the bulk of his fortune

01:17:43.458 --> 01:17:45.941
to the Bill and Melinda Gates
Foundation

01:17:46.141 --> 01:17:48.425
and giving more
than 15% of his money

01:17:48.625 --> 01:17:53.375
to foundations started by his three
children and his late wife, Susan.

01:17:53.575 --> 01:17:56.425
Man 2: One global health activist
called what Buffett did today

01:17:56.625 --> 01:18:02.383
one of the most remarkably selfless
acts that history will ever record.

01:18:02.583 --> 01:18:06.500
That's a better hand than I get
at a Berkshire Hathaway meeting.

01:18:06.700 --> 01:18:08.467
I'd like to thank you
for coming.

01:18:08.667 --> 01:18:12.959
It... it's a great day for me.
It's a great day for my family.

01:18:13.159 --> 01:18:16.208
My wife Susie and I had planned
that whatever I made

01:18:16.408 --> 01:18:17.675
would go back to society,

01:18:17.875 --> 01:18:20.250
and, originally, I thought
she would outlive me

01:18:20.450 --> 01:18:22.854
and that she'd make
a big decision on it.

01:18:23.054 --> 01:18:25.258
But since her death,
I had to rethink

01:18:25.458 --> 01:18:27.525
the best way to get
the money into society

01:18:27.725 --> 01:18:29.592
and have it used
in the most effective way,

01:18:29.792 --> 01:18:34.050
and I had a solution
staring me in the face.

01:18:34.250 --> 01:18:38.000
It was completely out of the blue.
I mean amazing.

01:18:38.200 --> 01:18:41.959
The largest single gift
ever given was

01:18:42.159 --> 01:18:44.550
what he gave away that day.

01:18:44.750 --> 01:18:47.583
I'd like to ask the people
representing those...

01:18:47.783 --> 01:18:49.667
various foundations
to come out.

01:18:53.583 --> 01:18:56.125
The first three letters are
easy to sign, I just sign "Dad."

01:18:59.458 --> 01:19:02.542
????

01:19:11.041 --> 01:19:13.166
Howard:
When he wrote the letter to us,

01:19:13.366 --> 01:19:14.634
he put something
in that letter

01:19:14.834 --> 01:19:16.342
that was
incredibly important to me,

01:19:16.542 --> 01:19:19.962
which was exactly how
our foundation behaves,

01:19:20.162 --> 01:19:22.898
which is,
if you're gonna try to bat a thousand,

01:19:23.098 --> 01:19:25.634
you won't do very many things
that are important.

01:19:25.834 --> 01:19:29.542
But if you're willing to
basically strike out a few times,

01:19:29.742 --> 01:19:32.542
you can really change
something big.

01:19:32.742 --> 01:19:35.342
I.C.C.N.!

01:19:35.542 --> 01:19:36.841
Warren: Well,
I feel terrific about the fact

01:19:37.041 --> 01:19:39.750
that my three children
each run a separate foundation

01:19:39.950 --> 01:19:42.583
that combines
their special interests,

01:19:42.783 --> 01:19:44.258
whether it's early education

01:19:44.458 --> 01:19:48.291
or whether it's farming in areas
where people's techniques for using

01:19:48.491 --> 01:19:51.208
small plots of land could use
a lot of improvement.

01:19:51.408 --> 01:19:53.417
All kinds of ways...
vaccines, you name it.

01:19:55.083 --> 01:19:56.550
Man:
More powerful than Buffett's gift

01:19:56.750 --> 01:19:59.917
is the message he's sending
to other wealthy Americans,

01:20:00.117 --> 01:20:02.562
that those who have
the least in this world

01:20:02.762 --> 01:20:05.208
should benefit from
those who have the most.

01:20:10.375 --> 01:20:13.291
Warren: In my entire lifetime,
everything that I've spent

01:20:13.491 --> 01:20:16.834
will be quite a bit less
than one percent

01:20:17.034 --> 01:20:17.675
of everything I've made.

01:20:17.875 --> 01:20:20.083
The other 99% plus
will go to others,

01:20:20.283 --> 01:20:22.291
because it has
no utility to me.

01:20:22.491 --> 01:20:24.208
????

01:20:26.375 --> 01:20:32.083
So, it's silly for me
to not transfer that utility

01:20:32.283 --> 01:20:33.542
to people who can use it.

01:20:35.417 --> 01:20:37.000
It's doing me no good.

01:20:42.166 --> 01:20:44.083
Susie Jr.:
I am so proud of what we do.

01:20:46.125 --> 01:20:47.592
I almost cry
at every board meeting,

01:20:47.792 --> 01:20:51.417
because I just think
she would be so proud.

01:20:52.750 --> 01:20:54.983
And that is my biggest job,
in my opinion,

01:20:55.183 --> 01:20:57.417
is to make sure
that every penny gets spent

01:20:57.617 --> 01:20:58.708
the way she would
want it spent.

01:21:01.959 --> 01:21:04.750
Susie: Whoever you are in this life,
you don't want to think

01:21:04.950 --> 01:21:09.083
you wasted a lot
of your energy, love,

01:21:09.283 --> 01:21:12.208
and time
on something useless.

01:21:12.408 --> 01:21:13.634
????

01:21:13.834 --> 01:21:17.500
I always thought I'd marry a minister,
a doctor, or somebody

01:21:17.700 --> 01:21:22.333
out doing
some valuable service

01:21:22.533 --> 01:21:24.217
to human beings.

01:21:24.417 --> 01:21:29.166
And the fact that I married somebody
who makes just piles of money

01:21:29.366 --> 01:21:32.500
is really the antithesis
of what I ever thought,

01:21:32.700 --> 01:21:34.500
but I know what he is,

01:21:34.700 --> 01:21:38.583
and... he is...

01:21:39.792 --> 01:21:42.375
There's no finer human being
than who he is.

01:21:44.792 --> 01:21:49.792
????

01:21:55.000 --> 01:21:56.817
Warren:
The truth is that I'm here

01:21:57.017 --> 01:21:58.846
in my position
as a matter of luck.

01:21:59.046 --> 01:22:00.875
Hey!
How are you doing, Grandpa?

01:22:01.075 --> 01:22:02.759
Hey, Grandpa!
Okay.

01:22:02.959 --> 01:22:04.759
Warren:
When I was born in 1930,

01:22:04.959 --> 01:22:09.717
the odds were probably 40:1 against
me being born in the United States.

01:22:09.917 --> 01:22:14.500
I did win the ovarian lottery on that
first day, and on top of that, I was male.

01:22:15.500 --> 01:22:17.133
Put that down
as another 50/50 shot

01:22:17.333 --> 01:22:22.500
and now the odds are 80:1 against being
born a male in the United States,

01:22:22.700 --> 01:22:26.000
and it was enormously
important in my whole life.

01:22:26.200 --> 01:22:29.300
To think that that makes me
superior to anyone else

01:22:29.500 --> 01:22:32.834
as a human being is just...
I can't follow that line of reasoning.

01:22:33.792 --> 01:22:35.458
Perfect!
Okay, good luck.

01:22:38.750 --> 01:22:43.250
I think I was lucky to have been
standing alongside Warren Buffett

01:22:43.450 --> 01:22:45.175
while he was
becoming Warren Buffett.

01:22:45.375 --> 01:22:50.542
He has developed over the years.
He's broadened.

01:22:50.742 --> 01:22:53.291
His values extend
through all of his life.

01:22:54.875 --> 01:22:57.592
He wants to lead a life
that he and his father,

01:22:57.792 --> 01:23:01.375
if his father was still living,
would say was a good one.

01:23:01.575 --> 01:23:03.217
????

01:23:03.417 --> 01:23:07.542
I think he's going to end up in the
history books a hundred years from now.

01:23:07.742 --> 01:23:10.791
I'm not sure what role
he's going to be assigned.

01:23:10.991 --> 01:23:14.041
Will he be famous
for what he did as an investor

01:23:14.241 --> 01:23:16.759
or as a philanthropist?

01:23:16.959 --> 01:23:21.375
But Warren said that his ambition
in life is to be a teacher.

01:23:22.875 --> 01:23:24.920
Warren:
The world is a great movie to watch,

01:23:25.120 --> 01:23:27.251
but you don't want
to sleepwalk through life.

01:23:27.451 --> 01:23:29.583
The important thing to do
is to look for the job

01:23:29.783 --> 01:23:31.834
you would take
if you didn't need a job

01:23:32.034 --> 01:23:33.717
and life is wonderful then.

01:23:33.917 --> 01:23:36.462
I mean, you'll jump out
of bed in the morning

01:23:36.662 --> 01:23:39.208
because you're really
looking forward to the day.

01:23:39.408 --> 01:23:42.634
I have...
for over 60 years,

01:23:42.834 --> 01:23:43.966
I've been able
to tap dance to work

01:23:44.166 --> 01:23:46.875
just 'cause I'm doing
what I love doing and...

01:23:47.075 --> 01:23:49.417
and I just feel
very, very lucky.

01:23:49.617 --> 01:23:51.500
Okay, class dismissed.

01:23:55.750 --> 01:23:58.291
????

01:24:11.333 --> 01:24:12.417
Night.

01:24:13.166 --> 01:24:14.625
Kunhardt:
Do you fear death?

01:24:14.825 --> 01:24:17.008
Warren:
No, I don't.

01:24:17.208 --> 01:24:20.834
I've had a terrific life.
I feel... you know, it's gonna happen,

01:24:21.034 --> 01:24:23.375
and I have no idea
what happens after it.

01:24:23.575 --> 01:24:24.675
I'm an agnostic, so I...

01:24:24.875 --> 01:24:26.841
you know, it may be
terribly interesting.

01:24:27.041 --> 01:24:28.834
It may not be interesting
at all. We'll find out.

